WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:03.068
<i>Previously on</i> reign...
Was it your gift

00:03.070 --> 00:06.171
Or your medicine
that healed me?
I saved your life.

00:06.173 --> 00:08.273
Say you'll marry me,
or we're over.
I can't.

00:08.275 --> 00:10.476
We may have
a promising future.

00:10.478 --> 00:12.277
Then let's see
if we're good together.

00:12.279 --> 00:15.080
Louis was approached by
elizabeth's envoy.

00:15.082 --> 00:17.583
You knew about this? That
condÃ© was courting England?

00:17.585 --> 00:20.219
Because he felt he had no
other choice. I abandoned him.

00:20.221 --> 00:22.021
Francis: <i>Do you realize</i>
<i>that by helping condÃ© escape,</i>

00:22.023 --> 00:24.656
<i>Elizabeth could have</i>
<i>a foothold in France?</i>

00:24.658 --> 00:26.125
CondÃ©'s army is
loyal to him.

00:26.127 --> 00:28.127
If he becomes king
consort of England,

00:28.129 --> 00:31.497
We will essentially have
an enemy army on our soil.

00:31.499 --> 00:34.166
Mary, this is the most dangerous
thing you have ever done.

00:34.168 --> 00:36.068
Akers: Her majesty
elizabeth still rejoices

00:36.070 --> 00:37.770
In the idea of marrying you.

00:37.772 --> 00:39.738
And she's ready to give you
her backing, if you take

00:39.740 --> 00:40.739
<i>The throne of France.</i>

00:40.741 --> 00:42.674
King louis of France!

00:42.676 --> 00:45.477
(men cheering)

00:49.149 --> 00:52.251
These are the regions where
lord condÃ© has been sighted.

00:52.253 --> 00:54.086
We've searched them all,
but found nothing.

00:54.088 --> 00:56.155
It's been four weeks
since condÃ© was last seen.

00:56.157 --> 00:57.589
You mean since
you helped him escape.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.825
My point is that

00:59.827 --> 01:01.560
He might not be
in France anymore.

01:01.562 --> 01:04.063
Our spies in England and abroad

01:04.065 --> 01:06.765
Haven't heard so much
as a whisper from him.

01:06.767 --> 01:08.534
He's still here.

01:08.536 --> 01:09.735
There are reports
some of his men

01:09.737 --> 01:11.236
Were seen
in the bouconne forest.

01:11.238 --> 01:12.838
He could be
gathering his troops.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.740
I want that forest searched.

01:14.742 --> 01:16.275
Take whoever you need.

01:18.745 --> 01:20.846
(door opens, closes)

01:20.848 --> 01:24.116
You think condÃ©'s a threat. Why?

01:24.118 --> 01:26.585
He's lost everything, there's
a warrant out for his head.

01:26.587 --> 01:28.387
Exactly. If I were him,
I'd want revenge.

01:28.389 --> 01:30.222
Whatever you think of him,
he's not vindictive.

01:30.224 --> 01:32.224
Maybe not to you.

01:32.226 --> 01:34.193
But I'm the one
who signed his death warrant.

01:34.195 --> 01:36.428
What could he have to gain
from striking out against you?

01:36.430 --> 01:38.764
The throne.

01:38.766 --> 01:40.399
He's a prince of the blood.

01:40.401 --> 01:43.135
All that stands between
him and the crown is my head.

01:43.137 --> 01:44.703
My brothers are
too young to rule,

01:44.705 --> 01:47.739
And no lords would accept
catherine as regent.

01:47.741 --> 01:49.408
You think condÃ© is
planning a coup.

01:49.410 --> 01:51.143
It's a prime opportunity.

01:51.145 --> 01:53.278
He has the support of the
english queen, who would like

01:53.280 --> 01:56.148
Nothing more than
to plunge France into chaos.

01:56.150 --> 01:57.583
And he knows
that we're vulnerable,

01:57.585 --> 01:59.418
What with the bulk of troops
in scotland

01:59.420 --> 02:01.320
Fighting to protect your throne.

02:01.322 --> 02:02.821
If you truly believe
that we are under threat,

02:02.823 --> 02:03.822
Then recall the troops.

02:03.824 --> 02:05.290
My throne in scotland

02:05.292 --> 02:06.558
Is meaningless
if France falls.

02:06.560 --> 02:08.227
I have considered it,
believe me,

02:08.229 --> 02:09.895
But bringing them back
would take too long.

02:09.897 --> 02:12.464
And it would look like
we're folding on another front.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.233
Then appeal to one of
your closer allies.

02:14.235 --> 02:15.300
Your brother-in-law,
king philip of Spain.

02:15.302 --> 02:17.302
I have, already.

02:17.304 --> 02:19.238
King philip is willing
to send troops,

02:19.240 --> 02:21.240
But only when there is
a clear and imminent threat.

02:21.242 --> 02:23.909
Not just my fears and
conjecture about what

02:23.911 --> 02:27.346
My wife's former lover might do.

02:27.348 --> 02:30.215
I understand your anger at me,

02:30.217 --> 02:32.251
But if you could
just look past it,

02:32.253 --> 02:34.186
You would see how sorry I am.

02:34.188 --> 02:36.488
Save your apologies.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.324
Your words have no meaning
for me anymore.

02:42.495 --> 02:44.596
(door opens)

02:50.537 --> 02:52.204
You weren't going to leave

02:52.206 --> 02:54.773
Without saying good-bye,
were you?

02:54.775 --> 02:57.376
It seemed a shame
to wake you.

02:57.378 --> 02:59.545
Do you have to go?

02:59.547 --> 03:01.680
If you stay, I can
make it worth your while.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.448
Tempting as that is,

03:03.450 --> 03:05.918
I doubt the king
would understand.

03:07.954 --> 03:09.254
Francis is relying
on your services

03:09.256 --> 03:10.856
More and more every day.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.525
You keep this up, you could
become his lead general.

03:16.296 --> 03:19.364
(moans softly)

03:19.366 --> 03:20.666
What?

03:20.668 --> 03:22.668
You're so beautiful.

03:22.670 --> 03:24.803
And I want to have my way
with you without worrying

03:24.805 --> 03:26.405
Who might see us.

03:26.407 --> 03:27.839
I thought that
added to the allure.

03:27.841 --> 03:29.374
It did, at first.

03:29.376 --> 03:31.643
But in the few weeks
we've had together,

03:31.645 --> 03:34.213
I've come to care for you.

03:34.215 --> 03:36.848
I see the life
I could have with you.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.350
Then I remember...

03:38.352 --> 03:40.953
You're married.
Well, that could change.

03:42.388 --> 03:43.789
Leave it to me.

03:43.791 --> 03:45.357
Once you return
victorious,

03:45.359 --> 03:47.359
Perhaps we'll both have
a change in status.

03:55.368 --> 03:56.568
(indistinct conversations)

03:56.570 --> 03:57.903
(goat bleating)

04:03.443 --> 04:04.810
Leith.

04:06.246 --> 04:09.314
It's been weeks
since we last spoke.

04:09.316 --> 04:10.582
I was beginning to think
you were avoiding me.

04:10.584 --> 04:12.784
Because I was. I am.

04:12.786 --> 04:14.653
But princess claude
insisted on

04:14.655 --> 04:16.288
A shopping trip to town.

04:16.290 --> 04:17.589
And what the princess
wants, she gets.

04:17.591 --> 04:20.259
Can I just say how sorry I am,

04:20.261 --> 04:22.327
About the way
things ended with us?

04:22.329 --> 04:24.363
How's business?

04:24.365 --> 04:26.665
Good. Thanks to your generosity.

04:26.667 --> 04:30.435
Actually, business is booming,
so I'll be able to pay you back.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.770
There's no need.

04:31.772 --> 04:34.406
I have no use
for the money.

04:34.408 --> 04:36.842
Not anymore.

04:52.325 --> 04:55.527
So, how are wedding plans
coming along?

04:55.529 --> 04:57.396
That's one perk
of being engaged to a madam,

04:57.398 --> 04:58.864
I bet she throws
a roaring party.

04:58.866 --> 05:01.767
Ready to return to the castle?

05:01.769 --> 05:03.335
Look at you, all business.

05:03.337 --> 05:05.437
Once you couldn't stop
talking about the epic,

05:05.439 --> 05:07.606
Insufferable love
you and greer share.

05:07.608 --> 05:09.474
Is the wedding
going to be in her whorehouse?

05:09.476 --> 05:11.343
With whore guests
and a whore officiant?

05:11.345 --> 05:13.979
If so, you have to invite me.

05:19.919 --> 05:21.320
I'm only teasing.

05:21.322 --> 05:22.421
But I am desperately curious

05:22.423 --> 05:23.755
About your upcoming nuptials.

05:23.757 --> 05:25.791
I command you
to give me details.

05:25.793 --> 05:29.728
You can command me to escort you
to every dress shop in town,

05:29.730 --> 05:31.697
Or to stand by your door
until I collapse.

05:31.699 --> 05:35.100
But there are some things that
even a princess has no claim to.

05:42.475 --> 05:44.476
Spruce bark.

05:44.478 --> 05:47.379
It's good for treating
infections and colds.

05:47.381 --> 05:49.548
You hunt, you trap,

05:49.550 --> 05:53.118
You bring people back
from the brink of death.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.487
You mean the ladies
at court can't do all that?

05:55.489 --> 05:58.890
Or read a man's past
and future by touching him?
(chuckles)

05:58.892 --> 06:01.059
They're more interested
in dancing and embroidery.

06:01.061 --> 06:04.429
But I think your skills
are far more useful.

06:04.431 --> 06:05.997
Well, I'm glad you think so.

06:05.999 --> 06:07.733
For the longest time,

06:07.735 --> 06:10.569
I prayed my gift
would be taken from me.

06:10.571 --> 06:12.037
Why?

06:12.039 --> 06:14.473
When I was a little girl,

06:14.475 --> 06:16.508
I saw the men in my village

06:16.510 --> 06:18.577
Drag a woman by her hair,

06:18.579 --> 06:20.879
Strap her to a post and...

06:20.881 --> 06:24.483
Plunge her into a freezing river
until she drowned.

06:24.485 --> 06:26.551
She was a midwife.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.987
But when one of the babies
she delivered was stillborn,

06:28.989 --> 06:31.022
The mother accused her
of using witchcraft.

06:31.024 --> 06:34.926
Said she stole
the baby's soul for the devil.

06:34.928 --> 06:38.897
Women who stick out
are apt to be killed.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.766
I suppose that's why
you've carved out

06:40.768 --> 06:42.567
A quiet life
for yourself.

06:42.569 --> 06:45.537
I've found it's best
to avoid people altogether.

06:45.539 --> 06:47.439
Must be lonely.

06:47.441 --> 06:49.508
You get used to it.

06:50.843 --> 06:52.878
You're a gifted seer,

06:52.880 --> 06:55.781
And there are places where your
talents would be appreciated.

06:55.783 --> 06:57.582
Do you know of nostradamus?

06:57.584 --> 06:59.684
I heard the queen mother herself
depended on his counsel.

06:59.686 --> 07:03.121
With him gone, the court
is in need of a new seer.

07:03.123 --> 07:05.524
Me? At court?

07:05.526 --> 07:06.992
You wouldn't
have to hide who you are

07:06.994 --> 07:09.094
Or what you do.
I doubt

07:09.096 --> 07:12.030
The court ladies would welcome
me into their embroidery group.

07:12.032 --> 07:13.598
You don't need them.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.133
You'd have me.

07:15.135 --> 07:16.668
At least
visit the castle,

07:16.670 --> 07:19.538
And see if it's a place
where you could be happy.

07:19.540 --> 07:22.808
I know I would be,
if I could...

07:22.810 --> 07:25.010
Look at your face
every day.

07:30.116 --> 07:33.618
â™ª I hear

07:34.787 --> 07:37.622
â™ª metal hearts

07:40.660 --> 07:42.727
â™ª clicking heels...

07:45.064 --> 07:47.599
(fast tempo acoustic
intro playing)

07:50.503 --> 07:52.804
â™ª they all need something

07:52.806 --> 07:57.676
â™ª to hold on to,
they all mean well â™ª

07:57.678 --> 08:01.179
â™ª you could never
feel my story â™ª

08:01.181 --> 08:05.116
â™ª it's all you know... Oh!

08:05.118 --> 08:08.487
